v.鼓舞，激励 【英】 v. 鼓舞，激励(to give vigor to; enliven; animate) 【考】 conducive : foment / tonic : invigorate / analgesic : deaden(助长的能煽动/激励 的能鼓舞/止痛的能消 痛)反义词：debilitate( 使虚弱); enervate(削弱); enfeeble(削弱) 【记】 in(使)+vigor(活力)+ ate→使有活力→鼓励 【例】 A quick breath of fresh air invigorate me. v. 使生气勃勃; 使有活力 = animate 【记】vigor(n 精力; 活力) 【类】tonic: invigorate = analgesic: deaden = conducive: foment滋补的使健壮 = 止痛的使麻木 = 导致的煽动 【反】pine(v 消瘦; 憔悴)－become invigorated(变得有活力); sap(v 使衰竭); emaciate(vt 使憔悴); demoralize(v 士气受挫)－invigorate『ameliorate』debilitate(vt 使衰弱); enervate(v 削弱); enfeeble(vt 使衰弱) 【记】in,en + vigor 【相关】vigor 精力, 活力, vigorous精力旺盛的 invigorate (v.)  1640s, from in- (2) + vigor + -ate (2). Earlier verb was envigor (1610s). Related: Invigorated; invigorating.
